        <p><strong>Open Programming Language</strong> (<strong>OPL</strong>) is an embedded programming language for portable devices that run the Symbian Operating System.</p>
        <p>The language was originally called <strong>Organiser Programming Language</strong>, developed by <strong>Psion Ltd</strong> for the {'Psion'|link_urls:'i'} Organiser.</p>
        <p>It can be found on the Nokia 9200, 9300 and 9500 Communicator series mobile telephone/personal digital assistant (PDA) and the Sony Ericsson P800, P900, P910 series.</p>
        <p>On classic Psion PDAs such as the Series 3, 5/5mx, Series 7, and netBook/netPad, as well as the MC218, OPL is part of the standard application suite.</p>
        <p>OPL is an interpreted language similar to {'BASIC'|link_urls:'/l'}.</p>
